comments.text: One of the first ever racing games of my life, alongside the classic NFS. Still love it because how underrated it is, and the bumper car-like physics that make it funny to drive.
comments.author: @diablow1411

comments.text: Probably the game that in the video has been runned in the software renderer not in hardware renderer and also due to the operating system incompatibility game doesn’t run properly. This is my view of course you know that.

comments.text: yes, the game was running in software render mode in the video

comments.text: 4:07 Looks like you skipped several events. You only did Cross and Monster on Rookie, but suddenly it says you did all of them, and are doing Semi-Pro Jump?
comments.author: @SirJorb

comments.text: I skipped some rookie events, because I did them before I had an idea to start recording a longplay and I figured it wasn't necessary to record those events since they're already unlocked when you start a new game, so anybody can check them out. In hindsight, I should have started a new game and done those events for completeness, but I can't do that now, because the video is uploaded and public already.
comments.author: @PAKTC

comments.text: So nostalgic with this game. Love this video.
comments.author: @BelluAA

comments.text: Thanks for sharing. Can you still play it today? Which Windows version do you use?
comments.author: @samidekash

comments.text: I used an earlier build of Windows 10 for this video, but had to enable Windows 95 compatibility mode to avoid crashes and physics glitches.
comments.author: @PAKTC

comments.text: @PAKTC   Just managed to play it on Windows 11. I used two versions of the game: First a full Installation file and then an ISO file to run in Window's virtual CD-ROM drive. Now it works smoothly, phantastic! Beetle party like it's 2000! 🤩 Thank you for bringing back childhood memories! ☺️
comments.author: @samidekash

comments.text: How can I play it with a USB Controller?
comments.author: @kalasatwater2224

comments.text: You need to map every button in options, also make sure you have DXInput capable controller (if your controller has multiple modes, switch to DXInput and restart the game), XInput doesn't work with this game
comments.author: @PAKTC

comments.text: @PAKTC  Thanks
